OL,7,FSpeaking to reporters after the
OL,8,Fmeeting, the two joint leaders of the
OL,9,Fadministration were asked about the
OL,10,Fissue of sentencing for perpetrators
OL,11,Fand whether they thought current jail
OL,12,Fterms were sufficient.
OL,14,FMs Little-Pengelly responded: "In
OL,15,Fterms of tougher sentences, I think
OL,16,Fyou'd probably find it hard to get an
OL,17,Fissue where I don't think there should
OL,18,Fbe tougher sentences. I do believe
OL,19,Fthat the law needs to be more muscular
OL,20,Fand robust when it comes to
OL,21,Fcriminality."
